1
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:15,240
I'm in...

2
00:00:15,570 --> 00:00:16,870
Jiang Tian's room.

3
00:00:18,020 --> 00:00:18,970
Where is he?

4
00:00:20,150 --> 00:00:22,280
Did we sleep in the same bed last night?

5
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,000
Good morning.

6
00:00:29,790 --> 00:00:30,640
Morning.

7
00:00:32,259 --> 00:00:33,030
So,

8
00:00:33,670 --> 00:00:35,930
did you sleep well in someone else's bed?

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,330
Don't be so petty. It's just one night.

10
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:39,670
So petty.

11
00:00:41,490 --> 00:00:42,890
I'm going back to my room.

12
00:00:43,330 --> 00:00:45,660
Am I running away after sleeping with him?

13
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:47,240
"Sleeping with him?"

14
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:48,500
What are you thinking?

15
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:50,900
Hey, Jiang Tian...

16
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:51,790
Huh?

17
00:00:52,540 --> 00:00:53,300
Where is he?

18
00:00:56,710 --> 00:00:58,840
Was he scared off by my morning wood?

19
00:00:59,910 --> 00:01:00,410
I don't believe

20
00:01:00,410 --> 00:01:02,610
that, as a healthy young adult,

21
00:01:02,660 --> 00:01:05,190
he wouldn't have morning wood when waking up.

22
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:08,710
I must be dreaming just now.

23
00:01:08,980 --> 00:01:10,350
Now that he's not here,

24
00:01:10,670 --> 00:01:12,070
I should better be going.

25
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:19,470
Why did I sleep here last night?

26
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,480
Can you black out even without drinking?

27
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,360
I wonder who was clinging to my bed

28
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:27,090
like a post-it note last night.

29
00:01:29,340 --> 00:01:31,280
Sometimes, when people are extremely tired,

30
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,539
they may feel a bit tipsy.

31
00:01:32,539 --> 00:01:33,830
You call that tipsy?

32
00:01:34,330 --> 00:01:36,789
That's more like being falling-down drunk.

33
00:01:36,950 --> 00:01:39,210
Can't you just forget about it? So petty.

34
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,310
Again?

35
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,560
Where did you sleep last night?

36
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,560
What do you think?

37
00:01:47,470 --> 00:01:48,950
There's only one bed here.

38
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,140
Where else can I sleep?

39
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:55,800
Right.

40
00:01:57,630 --> 00:02:00,230
Change your clothes and let's have breakfast.

41
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:03,030
Well...

42
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:05,320
Wait a moment. I'm not ready yet.

43
00:02:12,990 --> 00:02:14,850
I forgot my phone in the bathroom.

44
00:02:57,270 --> 00:02:59,910
[Happy Opening]

45
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:05,120
[Post-it]

46
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:52,380
[The On1y One]

47
00:03:52,810 --> 00:03:55,340
[Episode 7: Belonging
Let's Live on Campus Together]

48
00:03:56,990 --> 00:03:57,820
Sheng.

49
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:01,070
You've been changing your screen name quite often recently.

50
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:02,800
Why are you so interested in me?

51
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:03,850
I'm not the one who noticed it.

52
00:04:03,850 --> 00:04:05,030
It's Pepper...

53
00:04:05,990 --> 00:04:07,740
Gao Tianyang, what?

54
00:04:08,130 --> 00:04:09,570
Yeah, yeah. It is me who is up to no good.

55
00:04:09,570 --> 00:04:10,870
I've been staring at Sheng's screen name for no reason.

56
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:11,860
Is that okay?

57
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,780
-Our Sheng is handsome and good at studying.
-Shut up!

58
00:04:13,780 --> 00:04:16,579
Where can we find such a talented and handsome boy?

59
00:04:18,370 --> 00:04:19,600
The more I think about it, the more it makes sense.

60
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,040
Sheng, be gay,

61
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:23,460
so I can have a taste of puppy love.

62
00:04:29,530 --> 00:04:30,240
Get lost.

63
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:34,690
Good morning.

64
00:04:35,610 --> 00:04:37,490
Sorry to take up your morning self-study time

65
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:38,830
to handle something.

66
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:42,080
We still need to reselect the Excellent Model Students.

67
00:04:42,080 --> 00:04:43,480
Let's do a secret ballot.

68
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:46,150
Please distribute the paper for me.

69
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,450
Please write the name on it.

70
00:04:47,450 --> 00:04:48,830
Then, we don't have to write the names

71
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:50,610
of the students who were chosen last time.

72
00:04:50,610 --> 00:04:52,130
One more thing.

73
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:54,500
I mentioned the criteria for Excellent Model Students last time.

74
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,670
One spot will be selected from the class cadres,

75
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:58,450
another will be based on grades, and a third will go to the student
with the greatest improvement.

76
00:04:58,450 --> 00:04:59,540
As you all know,

77
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:03,120
Jiang Tian has held the No. 1 position in the grade for a long time,

78
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:06,570
and you can all see the great rise in Sheng Wang's ranking.

79
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:09,820
Originally, these two spots were supposed to be theirs.

80
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:11,250
However,

81
00:05:12,490 --> 00:05:13,700
these two students,

82
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,400
firstly, are very confident,

83
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:17,780
and secondly, they want to give others a chance.

84
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:20,180
So, they willingly give up these two spots.

85
00:05:24,910 --> 00:05:27,620
So, the spot will go to the students in second place.

86
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:28,280
Li Jia.

87
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:32,900
Your total score ranks second in the grade in two exams.

88
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:35,440
And I remember you had a high vote last time.

89
00:05:35,650 --> 00:05:37,370
Then, we'll give one spot to Li Jia.

90
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:39,100
Is that alright with everyone?

91
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:42,840
Thank you. Thank you, teacher.

92
00:05:42,860 --> 00:05:44,070
Pepper, good for you!

93
00:05:44,070 --> 00:05:45,490
Sit down.

94
00:05:45,930 --> 00:05:46,680
Sit down.

95
00:05:47,530 --> 00:05:48,710
Then, Gao Tianyang,

96
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:51,409
you've improved by 64 points compared to last time,

97
00:05:51,409 --> 00:05:54,110
and your rank has gone up by 78 places.

98
00:05:54,130 --> 00:05:56,659
You are the student with the second-most improved performance in the class.

99
00:05:56,659 --> 00:05:59,520
So, let's give the other spot to Gao Tianyang, okay?

100
00:06:00,070 --> 00:06:01,550
Darn it, me?

101
00:06:02,050 --> 00:06:03,830
Stop cursing. It's you.

102
00:06:06,530 --> 00:06:08,280
Sheng, thank you.

103
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,850
I'll give you a gift.

104
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:11,290
What gift?

105
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:11,990
Your hand.

106
00:06:13,690 --> 00:06:14,590
[Congratulations]

107
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:15,970
Congratulations.

108
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,900
All right, pass the paper to the front as soon as you're done.

109
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:20,180
Isn't there a saying

110
00:06:21,460 --> 00:06:24,310
that when two people no longer stand on ceremony with each other

111
00:06:24,310 --> 00:06:27,370
and can comfortably share both troubles and honors...

112
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:31,490
they are then friends?

113
00:06:32,290 --> 00:06:33,420
Why are you smiling?

114
00:07:25,740 --> 00:07:27,980
Then, I'll announce the voting results.

115
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:30,910
The spot selected from the class cadres is Li Yu.

116
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,200
The one who has received the most votes is Xu Tianshu.

117
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:34,659
Congratulations to them.

118
00:07:38,650 --> 00:07:40,159
Alright, I'll give you back the early self-study time.

119
00:07:40,159 --> 00:07:42,020
You guys do your exercise papers.

120
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:45,580
Hey, how about we go to the Little White House together later?

121
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,520
The teacher wants to see me after class.

122
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,780
You can go by yourself.

123
00:08:16,610 --> 00:08:18,820
I really need to talk to Jiang Tian.

124
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,380
Go. Leave!

125
00:08:20,580 --> 00:08:21,920
Don't come here again!

126
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:23,490
Don't let me see you!

127
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:25,210
How many times do I have to ask?

128
00:08:25,210 --> 00:08:26,490
You won't stop talking.

129
00:08:26,490 --> 00:08:27,690
You old stubborn man.

130
00:08:39,610 --> 00:08:40,409
Grandpa Ding!

131
00:08:41,110 --> 00:08:41,909
You're here.

132
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:44,380
Why do I feel you're so down today?

133
00:08:44,410 --> 00:08:45,560
I'm not welcome here?

134
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:48,150
No, the food is ready.

135
00:08:49,030 --> 00:08:49,910
Where is Tian?

136
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:54,280
He can't come because of something at school.

137
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:56,230
Luckily.

138
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:58,470
It's good that he didn't come.

139
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,220
Oh, right.

140
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,840
Who's that man...

141
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:04,570
who just left just now?

142
00:09:07,490 --> 00:09:08,900
You saw the man?

143
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:10,120
Yeah.

144
00:09:10,370 --> 00:09:11,560
He passed me by.

145
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:16,850
That's Ji Huanyu.

146
00:09:19,580 --> 00:09:21,080
Ji Huanyu?

147
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:24,330
Tian's dad.

148
00:09:24,570 --> 00:09:26,970
Oh, right. My dad told me about it.

149
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,350
He used to live here too.

150
00:09:34,070 --> 00:09:35,280
Can I have a look?

151
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:38,100
Here.

152
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:48,040
These photos

153
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,020
are a bit old.

154
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,600
You young people don't get photos developed anymore, right?

155
00:10:04,650 --> 00:10:05,730
Who is this person?

156
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:07,970
That's two different people.

157
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:09,110
Oh, right.

158
00:10:09,130 --> 00:10:11,630
No wonder one's a color photo and the other's black-and-white.

159
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:14,160
They feel like they are from a different time.

160
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:15,640
This cat

161
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:19,140
seems to be the one Jiang Tian used as his profile photo.

162
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:21,230
I think so.

163
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:24,380
So, this is Jiang Tian?

164
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:25,660
Uh-huh.

165
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:32,240
Then this man...

166
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:39,570
Ji Huanyu.

167
00:10:44,070 --> 00:10:46,840
Ji Huanyu is really not a good man.

168
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:51,760
Tian had a difficult childhood with him when he was little.

169
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,620
Tian wasn't happy

170
00:10:56,650 --> 00:10:57,950
when he was little?

171
00:10:58,360 --> 00:11:00,530
Unhappy and had a tough life.

172
00:11:01,620 --> 00:11:03,370
Just like a stray cat.

173
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:08,110
When Tian was little,

174
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,430
Ji Huanyu

175
00:11:10,820 --> 00:11:11,910
and Tian's mother

176
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:13,910
were always away and busy.

177
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:17,280
So, they sent him to his grandmother.

178
00:11:19,990 --> 00:11:22,030
His grandmother had Alzheimer's.

179
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:25,000
She often locked Tian out and didn't let him in.

180
00:11:25,020 --> 00:11:26,110
Grandma!

181
00:11:28,010 --> 00:11:29,010
Grandma!

182
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,280
Grandma!

183
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:38,490
Tian would sit outside the door all day,

184
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:39,840
having nothing to eat.

185
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:42,880
He was shy

186
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:45,650
and didn't want others to know that he was locked out

187
00:11:45,650 --> 00:11:47,580
and didn't want to disturb others.

188
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:00,360
At that time, I had a cat named "Captain."

189
00:12:00,710 --> 00:12:03,150
Sometimes, when Tian couldn't get into the house,

190
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:04,530
he would play with Captain

191
00:12:04,530 --> 00:12:05,900
at the door.

192
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:07,270
And I'd take this chance

193
00:12:07,420 --> 00:12:09,090
to bring Tian back to my home

194
00:12:09,130 --> 00:12:10,200
so that he could

195
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:11,510
have something to eat.

196
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:13,470
I was looking for my cat.

197
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:15,360
So, you have it.

198
00:12:15,990 --> 00:12:18,410
Grandpa, what's the name of this cat?

199
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:21,500
Its name is Captain. Is it a good name?

200
00:12:21,530 --> 00:12:22,820
Yes.

201
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:25,640
Why don't you go inside?

202
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,040
Your grandma is not home?

203
00:12:31,260 --> 00:12:33,720
Then, how about coming to my place and waiting for her again?

204
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,100
Okay.

205
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:35,140
Okay, let's go.

206
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,800
Hold it tightly. I'll take your bag for you.

207
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,650
You're hungry, right?

208
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:11,840
Captain was a stray cat.

209
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:15,630
I think Tian was so close to the cat

210
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:18,590
because he probably felt they were similar.

211
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,370
What about Captain?

212
00:13:22,570 --> 00:13:23,530
It's dead.

213
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,410
Captain lived outdoors.

214
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:27,990
Tian

215
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:29,800
would often wait for it outside,

216
00:13:30,070 --> 00:13:31,600
waiting for it to come back.

217
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,330
He told me

218
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:37,690
that as long as he waited there, Captain would come back.

219
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:40,110
But the cat never came back.

220
00:13:47,370 --> 00:13:49,060
Seeing Jiang Tian so lonely

221
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:53,070
must have made Auntie Jiang very sad, right?

222
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:56,460
You know Jiang?

223
00:13:57,740 --> 00:14:00,580
Oh, yes, that...

224
00:14:00,860 --> 00:14:04,290
Actually, Auntie Jiang is sort of with my dad now.

225
00:14:04,330 --> 00:14:05,870
They may get married soon.

226
00:14:07,330 --> 00:14:08,750
Right, right.

227
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:11,050
I heard about it, but I forgot.

228
00:14:12,070 --> 00:14:16,360
So, you and Tian are kind of brothers now.

229
00:14:19,830 --> 00:14:20,780
Sort of.

230
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:27,440
It's good for Jiang to have a new boyfriend.

231
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,280
I watched her grow up.

232
00:14:30,990 --> 00:14:33,310
She was diligent and filial when she was young.

233
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:34,960
She had a lot of jobs

234
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:38,470
to pay for her mother's medical expenses and support Tian.

235
00:14:39,330 --> 00:14:42,450
She had a lot of side jobs in Taipei too.

236
00:14:43,790 --> 00:14:46,650
But she just didn't have the time to accompany Tian,

237
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:48,220
so she felt very guilty.

238
00:14:48,850 --> 00:14:51,350
Sometimes, when she came back to see Tian,

239
00:14:51,370 --> 00:14:55,100
her eyes were so swollen from crying that they looked like walnuts.

240
00:14:56,530 --> 00:14:58,930
Jiang Tian had such a miserable childhood.

241
00:14:59,710 --> 00:15:01,090
What about his father?

242
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:08,200
He...

243
00:15:09,650 --> 00:15:11,190
He is an orphan.

244
00:15:11,990 --> 00:15:14,870
He was often bullied when he was young.

245
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:17,730
When he grew up,

246
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:21,420
he wanted to do big things and achieve something.

247
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:24,320
In the end, he couldn't do anything well

248
00:15:25,580 --> 00:15:28,380
and was unwilling to take care of his child at home.

249
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:32,290
One time, he suddenly changed

250
00:15:32,520 --> 00:15:34,450
and came back to accompany Tian.

251
00:15:34,470 --> 00:15:36,470
He accompanied him for a whole year.

252
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:39,160
Isn't that good?

253
00:15:39,430 --> 00:15:41,100
Not at all.

254
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:43,380
He didn't know how to take care of a child.

255
00:15:44,190 --> 00:15:45,110
One day,

256
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:46,670
Tian came to my house,

257
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:49,810
and I found a burn on the back of his neck.

258
00:15:51,890 --> 00:15:53,210
A few days later,

259
00:15:53,300 --> 00:15:55,630
he had a fever and vomited at my house.

260
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:59,470
Then Jiang took him back.

261
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:01,560
Soon after,

262
00:16:01,990 --> 00:16:03,920
she divorced Ji Huanyu.

263
00:16:06,140 --> 00:16:10,180
About that scar on his neck, was it Ji...

264
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:12,670
That's what I asked him.

265
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:14,180
He said no.

266
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:15,970
I think

267
00:16:16,870 --> 00:16:19,120
he didn't want to tell me the truth.

268
00:16:21,470 --> 00:16:22,770
That's how he is.

269
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:23,990
He won't say anything

270
00:16:23,990 --> 00:16:26,190
and will take everything upon himself.

271
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,350
Later,

272
00:16:29,610 --> 00:16:31,990
I don't know why

273
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:33,820
but Tian wandered around.

274
00:16:34,210 --> 00:16:36,540
He'd live with people who had a spare room.

275
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:39,230
I often saw him carrying luggage,

276
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:42,860
crashing at someone's house here or there.

277
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,940
He couldn't be close to anyone,

278
00:16:47,230 --> 00:16:49,030
and no one could keep him around.

